text:
I recently became the owner of Fitbit Charge 5, and I was also the owner of Charge 3 and 4. I still have the scale from Fitbit and a VISA from Fitbit. That's why I can judge the bracelet correctly and compare it with predecessors. So let's go!
Positives:
1. The bracelet is stylish, fits perfectly on the wrist and very light;
2. The display has the same colour and is very easy to read, touch screen works smoothly, the screen protects Gorilla glass - is absolutely sufficient for normal use;
3. work;
4. Charging the bracelet has become much better and easier compared to Charge 4 (not a clip, but a magnet);
5. 6 months of premium membership is free;
6. Visa payment always works smoothly.
Negatives:
1. battery lasts less than with Charge 4 (before it was about 7 days, with a new bracelet just under 4);
2. clutch to the mobile phone is sometimes problematic (about 1 out of 3 clutches it doesn't work - annoying);
3. Functions: - GPS has strong deviations from the mobile phone (just like with its predecessor), pulse measurement is a bit got worse (I always compare with a professional heart rate monitor, with the new bracelet you have to pay a lot of attention to the bracelet position (there was no problem with predecessors), recognition of sports exercises has become worse;
4. Although the silicone bracelet has become softer, in my opinion, has become more uncomfortable;
5. Membership is free for 6 months and then? Why do you have to pay for normal services? The same services (evaluation of your health values), but free of charge, are offered by several manufacturers of competitor brands.

Conclusion: if you want to look stylish and know a little more about yourself - then the Fitbit offer is made for you! If you are a passionate athlete or even a semi-professional - then you better look for something else.
